
XHR / AJAX (Very Short): XHR is a browser feature for making asynchronous requests, and AJAX is the technique that uses it to update web content without full page reloads.






XMLHttpRequest
Asynchronous JavaScript and XML


 XHR is the method your web browser uses to communicate with the server, while AJAX is the overall technique that allows your web page to update content without needing to reload the entire page.